│ THOUGHT: The VPlan and legacy models are cost-tied for different VFs, and the current isMoreProfitable comparator only uses a strict per-lane cost comparison. Because vectorFactors()    │
│ are often iterated in descending VF order, ties keep the first (larger) VF, leading to VF=8 instead of the expected VF=4 in the test. I’ll modify the comparator to explicitly add a      │
│ tie-break: when normalized costs are equal, prefer scalable VFs if allowed (preserving existing scalable preference), otherwise prefer the smaller fixed VF. This change aligns VPlan     │
│ decisions with the legacy model without touching assertions.                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│ python3 - <<'PY' && submit-patch                                                                                                                                                          │
│ import re, sys                                                                                                                                                                            │
│ p = 'llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/LoopVectorize.cpp'                                                                                                                                     │
│ with open(p,'r') as f:                                                                                                                                                                    │
│     s=f.read()                                                                                                                                                                            │
│                                                                                                                                                                                           │
│ # Locate the isMoreProfitable(A,B,MaxTripCount) comparator and its early return when !MaxTripCount.                                                                                       │
